# Home Assistant Blueprints

This repository contains blueprints for Home Assistant, which provide pre-configured automations that you can easily import and use in your Home Assistant instance.

## How to Use the Blueprints

1. **Open Home Assistant**: Navigate to your Home Assistant instance.

2. **Go to Blueprints**: In the sidebar, click on "Settings" and then "Automations & scenes".

3. **Import a Blueprint**: After switching to the "Blueprints" tab, click on the "Import Blueprint" button in the bottom right corner.

4. **Enter Blueprint URL**: Copy the URL of the blueprint you want to use from this repository and paste it into the input field. For example, to import the Philips Tap Dial Switch ZHA blueprint, use the following URL:

    https://github.com/nickcwilkins/hass-blueprints/blob/main/hue/tap_dial_zha.yaml

5. **Follow the Prompts**: After importing, follow the prompts to configure the blueprint with your specific devices and preferences.

## Available Blueprints

| Blueprint Name | Description | File |
|----------------|-------------|------|
| Philips Tap Dial Switch ZHA | Fully featured automation for controlling the four-button Philips Hue Tap Dial Switch via Zigbee Home Automation. Dial and Long Presses are supported and will control all lights currently turned on that are designated with "Allow Dimming". | [hue/tap_dial_zha.yaml](https://github.com/nickcwilkins/hue/tap_dial_zha.yaml) |

For more information on each blueprint, refer to the comments and documentation within the respective YAML files.

